,\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Understanding Docker Networking and Testing**\\n\\nI'm considering how the Docs mention that the runner disables Docker networking after pre-pulling. This could mean that local Docker containers might not have external network access, which raises the question of whether I need extra dependencies, like Testcontainers. However, the normal scaffold doesn’t include Testcontainers; if I’m using Docker, I'll need a way for tests to interact. Also, for JUnit 5 with Testcontainers, I might need to add the org.testcontainers:neo4j dependency. I'll need to search for required Docker images to figure this out.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_YVlZZtYufi68qu8TRyQ8jscQ|fc_037ff3bfaf2c2296016a4225913f288194b06a60f3acd063b6", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src -name required-docker-images.txt -print | head -20 | xargs -r -n1 sh -c 'echo --- $0; cat $0; dirname $0'", "timeout": 20}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1662, "output": 411, "cacheRead": 35840, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 37913, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782719880728, "responseId": "resp_037ff3bfaf2c2296016a4225894438819497baeb2c84ac50e9"}}
